Env * env = init_env()

Detailed Description

Evaluate the s-expression tree parsed by parse.cpp and do error detection.

Function Documentation

Cell * apply ( Cell *  proce,
Cell *  args 
)

Apply proce with args as its formals arguments list.

Returns:
The value of applying the function to args.

Push a new frame whose parents is the top frame currently in the env. Bind args to proce's formal parameter list.

pop previous calling stacks when exceptions ocurr in user defined functions. to make the calling stack properly pop.

void check_formals ( Cell *  formals  ) 

Check if formals is a well-formed formal parameter list. Throw an error if formals is not a well-formed list or formals contains same name.

Parameters:
formals The formal parameter list to be checked.

Check if string name conflict with names already in the formal parameter list. If so, throw an error.

Parameters:

raise the error, if the first operand is of wrong type.
